				<p style="text-align:center;">Use Plate Method to Estimate the amount of different classes of foods.<br><img src="plate_habit.jpg"></img><br></p>
				<p style="text-align:left;">
				Divide your plate into 3 sections.
				<br>1. ¼ of the place for a piece of meat, poultry or fish.
				<br>2. Another ¼ for starch (potato, rice, noodles, corn, or bread).
				<br>3. The remaining ½ for vegetables.
				<br>4. Your fruit and beverage are next to your plate.
				<br>5. If you have more carbohydrate allowed in your meal plan, have milk, yogurt or something from the sweets list.
				<br>6. Salad vegetables are free but count the dressing.
